### Description

I am using the builder option to embed some assets inside my application:
```
"architect": {
	"build": {
		"options": {
			"outputPath": "dist",
			"assets": [
				"src/favicon.ico",
				"src/assets"
			]
		}
	}
}
```

This was working flawlessly to copy all the file and folder hierarchy of `src/assets` into `dist` until I needed to add an empty sub-directory to the assets: `src/assets/EmptyDir`. Now everything else in `src/assets` is still copied properly, but `src/assets/EmptyDir` is not.

I need this empty directory to be embedded in the application as well and I couldn't find a syntax to make it work so far, even adding the path to the exmpty folder explicitly didn't work, it is still ignored:
```
"options": {
	"outputPath": "dist",
	"assets": [
		"src/favicon.ico",
		"src/assets",
                "src/assets/EmptyDir"
	]
}
```

## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction

- Make a project with an empty directory in `src/assets/EmptyDir` and the build configuration above.
- Run `ng build --prod`
- Notice that `EmptyDir` is not copied in `dist`.

## üî• Exception or Error

No error that I could see.

